A body was found in an abandoned home in Pinellas Park on Wednesday, according to police. Officers were called to a residence located in the 6000 block of Park Boulevard around 12:20 p.m., the Pinellas Park Police Department said in a news release Wednesday evening. Inside the home, they found the body of a male. Police described the death as “suspicious.” They did not provide the male’s age, name or any other details. “This investigation is active, and no other information will be released until the conclusion of the investigation,” the release said. This is a developing story. Stay with tampabay.com for updates.